node.text: You will get to see it all on @peacocktv and @wwenetwork tonight at 5pm PST. It’s an incredible honor to be apart of the WWE Hall of Fame Class of 2020. To be apart of so many iconic WWE Superstars. I’ll be spamming you all later because I have so many people to thank, who have been apart of this incredible, memorable, historic journey.  This doesn’t mean the end, just a reflection of the past, a celebration of achievements, honors and barriers broken, and a beginning of a new chapter in an era where Mom’s are totally kicking ass! In our home that we call WWE we get to wear many masks. No matter my next one, in ring or out, it will always remain Fearless and with my ICONIC BELLA ARMY. Like us Bellas and the Bella Army have said from the beginning, We Run It, We Rule It and Haters Gonna Hate, Bellas Gonna Ball. Excited to share tonight with you all!! And even more excited that there will be more women competing at WrestleMania! We should never doubt the presence of women on the card, RAW, SmackDown, or PPV’s. Those days are done. Let’s do better. Let’s keep the equality going. We need and WANT more women matches and stories! And remember WWE Universe you are a huge part of that! Keep supporting women’s wrestling! Love you all!

node.text: minutes to watch. Also, please share it on your platforms too. I don’t know about you but this pandemic has definitely changed me. It has definitely been “The Great Realization” I needed. I’m looking at life so differently. What’s truly important to me. What I truly want to do with my time that I’m so grateful to have. Appreciating Mother Nature more in so many different ways. Living more simple. Truly putting my soon to be family first, even before a career I have made. Having more FaceTime and conversations with my loved ones that I miss. And truly giving my undivided attention to the ones that I sit with. Being picky about the people that surround me. Do they bring me joy, positivity and glee? I found this video so perfectly said and true. I hope we, as a world, do change after this and become renewed. And when we get opportunities to help with change we remember this time we all had to go through. We all remember how beautiful Mother Nature grew. We remember that we were in it together, even with different views. And we still help out the people less fortunate than us and still clap to say thank you. I truly hope after this, as a world, we don’t go back to our old ways. We remember what has happened and the hope for better days. I can definitely say that once we heal, it makes me excited, to experience a world so new with all of you. ❤️🌎🦋✨ @probablytomfoolery

node.text: Talk about the ultimate #sistersunday weekend! Had such an incredible 3 days at @bottlerocknapa 🤘🏼✨🎸 @bonitabonitawine exceeded all expectations and I am just so beyond grateful!! Thank you for helping make our Bella dreams come true!! Here’s to Bonita Bonita satisfying palates and spreading the love everywhere! Love that you all loved our @margot_van_huijkelom art exhibit! We are always wanting to bring a piece of Paris to you! She’s my fav! Until next year BottleRock! Peace and love! ☮️🕊✌🏼🤍✨🥂🤘🏼🎸🍑🌸👯‍♀️❤️‍🔥 #bonitabonita
